label.value: Liver Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v6

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of liver cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system. TNM clinical findings are based on information obtained prior to the first definitive treatment through physical examination, diagnostic imaging, and biopsy.

label.value: Liver Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of liver cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system. TNM pathologic findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

label.value: Liver Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of liver cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

label.value: Liver Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of liver cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes. TNM pathologic regional lymph nodes findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

label.value: Liver Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of liver cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. TNM pathologic distant metastasis findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

label.value: Liver Cancer pTX TNM Finding v6

value.value: Liver cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Ciliary Body Spindle Cell Melanoma

value.value: A melanoma that arises from the ciliary body. It is characterized by the presence of spindle-shaped melanocytes.

label.value: Liver Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Liver cancer with no evidence of a primary tumor. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Liver Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Liver cancer with a solitary tumor of any size without vascular invasion. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Liver Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Liver cancer with a solitary tumor of any size with vascular invasion, or with multiple tumors none of which are more than 5 cm in size. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Liver Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Liver cancer with multiple tumors at least one of which is more than 5 cm in size, or a tumor involving a major branch of the portal or hepatic vein. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Liver Cancer pT4 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Liver cancer with tumor(s) invading adjacent organs other than the gallbladder or with tumor perforating the visceral peritoneum. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Liver Cancer pNX TNM Finding v6

value.value: Liver cancer in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Liver Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Liver cancer with no regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Liver Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Liver cancer with regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Liver Cancer pMX TNM Finding v6

value.value: Liver cancer in which distant metastasis cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Liver Cancer pM0 TNM Finding

value.value: Liver cancer with no evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Ciliary Body Intermediate Cell Type Melanoma

value.value: Ciliary body melanoma characterized by the presence of intermediate cells which are similar to but smaller than epithelioid cells.

label.value: Liver Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Liver cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pTX TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Gastric cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Gastric cancer with no evidence of a primary tumor. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pTis TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Gastric cancer in situ with cancer cells confined within the glandular basement membrane (intraepithelial) and without invasion into the lamina propria. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Gastric cancer with tumor invading the lamina propria or submucosa. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Gastric cancer with tumor invading the muscularis propria or subserosa. A tumor may penetrate the muscularis propria with extension into the gastrocolic or gastrohepatic ligaments, or into the greater or lesser omentum, without perforation of the visceral peritoneum covering these structures. In this case, the tumor is classified T2. If there is perforation of the visceral peritoneum covering the gastric ligaments or the omentum, the tumor should be classified T3. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Applicant

value.value: A person who requests or seeks something such as assistance or employment or admission.

label.value: Gastric Cancer pT2a TNM Finding v6

value.value: Gastric cancer with tumor invading the muscularis propria. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pT2b TNM Finding v6

value.value: Gastric cancer with tumor invading the subserosa. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Gastric cancer with tumor penetrating the serosa (visceral peritoneum) without invasion into adjacent structures of the stomach. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Ciliary Body Epithelioid Cell Melanoma

value.value: A ciliary body melanoma characterized by the presence of malignant large epithelioid melanocytes.

label.value: Gastric Cancer pT4 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Gastric cancer with tumor invading into adjacent structures of the stomach which include the spleen, transverse colon, liver, diaphragm, pancreas, abdominal wall, adrenal gland, kidney, small intestine, and retroperitoneum. Intramural extension into the esophagus or duodenum is classified by the depth of the greatest invasion in any of these sites, including the stomach. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pNX TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Gastric cancer in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Gastric cancer with no evidence of metastasis to regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Gastric cancer with evidence of metastasis in 1-6 regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pN2 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Gastric cancer with evidence of metastasis in 7-15 regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pN3 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Gastric cancer with evidence of metastasis in more than 15 regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pMX TNM Finding v6

value.value: Gastric cancer in which distant metastasis cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pM0 TNM Finding

value.value: Gastric cancer with no evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Gastric cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Gene Transfer or Gene Delivery Agent

value.value: Genetic engineered recombinant products, including viral or non-viral based system that can be used to transfer genetic materials of interest into cells for either research or clinical purpose.

label.value: Recombinant Luteinizing Hormone

value.value: Any recombinant form of the endogenously produced heterodimer glycoprotein luteinizing hormone (LH) normally made by the anterior pituitary gland, that can be used for the treatment of LH deficiency. Upon administration, recombinant LH mimics the biological activity of endogenous LH. In females, this triggers ovulation and the development of the corpus luteum. In males, LH stimulates Leydig cells to produce testosterone.

label.value: Conjunctival Squamous Intraepithelial Neoplasia

value.value: A precancerous neoplastic intraepithelial process involving the conjunctival squamous epithelium.
